# shawn-cao.github.io

Personal blog and portfolio hosted on **GitHub Pages** (`Shawn-Cao/shawn-cao.github.io`).

## Workflow

- **No local builds.** The owner does not run Jekyll locally; changes are validated by **pushing to GitHub and checking production** at https://shawn-cao.github.io/
- Do not suggest `bundle install`, `jekyll serve`, or Ruby setup unless the user explicitly asks for local development.
- After content or config edits, remind them to push and verify on the live site if relevant.

## Stack

- **Jekyll 3.10** via GitHub’s built-in Pages builder (`github-pages` gem **~232**, Ruby **3.3.4** on GitHub).
- Production dependency versions: https://pages.github.com/versions.json
- **Pixyll** theme is **vendored** in-repo (`_layouts/`, `_includes/`, `_sass/`), not `remote_theme`.
- `Gemfile` only declares `github-pages`. `Gemfile.lock` is gitignored.

## Key paths

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `_posts/` | Blog posts (`YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md`) |
| `_drafts/` | Unpublished drafts |
| `_config.yml` | Site config, plugins, Disqus |
| `_includes/navigation.html` | Header nav links |
| `_layouts/`, `_includes/`, `_sass/` | Theme |

## Config notes

- `markdown: kramdown`, `permalink: pretty`, `paginate: 4`
- Plugins: `jekyll-paginate`, `jekyll-sitemap` (use `plugins:` in `_config.yml`; `gems:` is deprecated but still works on GHP)
- Disqus: `disqus_shortname` in `_config.yml`, embed in `_layouts/post.html`

## Out of scope unless asked

- **`app/`**, **`presentations/`**, **`movie/`** — legacy demos/static assets, not part of the Jekyll blog build.
- **Jekyll 4** or **GitHub Actions** migration — only if the user requests leaving branch-built Pages.
- Large refactors of legacy Angular/Bower code under `app/`.

## Related projects

- **`/player-chooser/`** — linked from `_includes/navigation.html` and blog posts. **Not in this repo.** Source and deploy: [Shawn-Cao/player-chooser](https://github.com/Shawn-Cao/player-chooser) (separate GitHub Pages site at https://shawn-cao.github.io/player-chooser/). Edit that repo for app changes; only change nav/links here.

## Gotchas

- Do not create git commits unless the user asks.
